article.headline: Kent St. 82, Youngstown St. 74
article.story: KENT, Ohio -- Al Fisher scored 20 points to lead Kent State to an 82-74 victory over Youngstown State on Monday night. Chris Singletary added 14 points and Anthony Simpson had 11 points to push Kent State (4-5) to a win in the second half. The game remained close until Kent State's Julian Sullinger broke a 40-40 tie with a layup with 15:39 left. The Golden Flashes never looked back, their lead surging to 21 points with 5:48 to go. Vance Cooksey was the game's leading scorer with 24 points off the bench for the Penguins (1-6). Kelvin Bright added 21 points for Youngstown State.
